<doc id="554284" wikidata="Q2471564" url="?curid=554284" title="USS White Plains">
<text>Two ships of the United States Navy have been named USS &quot;White Plains&quot;, after the Battle of White Plains during the American Revolutionary War.

* The first was an escort carrier in service from 1943 to 1946, and notable for action in the Battle off Samar.
* The second was a combat stores ship in service from 1968 to 1995.</text><links>
